 at Doddabettahalli\r\n•\t07 MLD STP at Jakkur\r\n•\t06 MLD STP at Yelahankakere\r\n\t•\tAs per requirement\t4 sets (1 for each STP)\r\n6\tPLC & SCADA for SBR System\t•\t17 MLD STP at Bilishivalli\r\n•\t07 MLD STP at Doddabettahalli\r\n•\t07 MLD STP at Jakkur\r\n•\t06 MLD STP at Yelahankakere\r\n\tAs per Requirement\t4 sets (1 for each STP)\r\n6\tDesign Package\t\t•\tP&ID diagram for Seller’s Major Components. \r\n•\tComplete SBR design package including, pumps, blowers, tanks, decanters and all SBR related items.\r\n•\tHydraulic calculations for SBR System\r\n•\tProcess Flow Diagram\r\n•\tControl Philosophy\r\n•\tSimulation Model of process design by using Biowin software.\r\n•\tPlot plan showing 2-D overhead view of equipment layout position, hydraulic and power Connections.\r\n•\tCivil GA of SBR Tank in all aspect.\r\n•\tAnchoring instruction/  foundation details of the SBR system.\r\n•\tEquipment List, datasheet/ specification for the SBR system.\r\n•\tMechanical GA, QAP and Technical Datasheets for Decanters\r\n•\tOperating sequence description for the SBR. Operation Philosophy\r\nEngineering information shall be submitted electronically in .doc or .docx file format. Engineering drawings will also be supplied in AutoCad file format.\t1 Lot\r\n7\tStartup\t\tStart-up document package will include Pre-installation checklist, Log-sheet formats, Sign-Off On Quantity (SBR Components List) and Quality(Treated water effluent quality at the outlet of SBR), Service Package (Equipment Manuals, Catalogues, Operation & Maintenance manuals for overall system), Punch list tracking spreadsheet. Start-up services include:\r\nEquipment Installation Technical Advisory Services as per site requirement for all 4 nos of STPs: SFC will provide all the necessary guidelines for unloading the equipment, rigging the equipment into place, installing interconnecting piping, installing interconnecting wiring, installing power wiring as applicable, testing for adequate water and air pressure, testing power supply, and testing interconnecting wire circuitry. PEEIL shall provide all actual labor.\r\nPre-start-up Inspection Visit: Includes time to time inspect installation work, address questions, develop punch list of completion items necessary prior to return visit.\r\nEquipment Start-up: Includes technical advisory services in  preparing the equipment to operate I/O verification, equipment manually, I/O verifications, operating the equipment automatically, testing control system, technical advisory services in support of SBR system. \r\nPEEIL shall arrange a storage area suitable for storage of SBR system components and shall unload the material and put it in store under supervision of SFC. \r\nPerformance Test – Includes technical advisory servicesin support of set-up of and witness performance test of 72 hours / 3 days continuous operating run (for Decanter) without intervention beyond normal operational activities. \r\nFormal Training: This includes formal training that typically takes place after the equipment has been started up and prior to putting the system into service. This does not include informal training that takes place during Equipment start-up with an operator being present and assisting the technicians performing start-up.\t1 Lot\r\n8\tO&M Manuals\t\tOperating and Maintenance Manual which includes Storage Procedures, Erection, commissioning and start-up procedures, Spare parts list, special tools list, Test-Run procedure, Trouble shooting procedure, Equipment Data sheets, Control Narrative, Control Logic summary chart, Operation sequence chart, drawings and datasheet, O&M Manuals, If Applicable.\r\nO&M manual shall be submitted electronically in .doc or .docx or pdf file format, written in English.\t1 Lot\r\n9\tProject schedule and management\t\t•\tDetailing Engineering, Procurement and Manufacturing Schedule.\r\n•\tDedicated Project Manager who will serve as the primary contact for the Buyer throughout the order execution and system commissioning of SBR system.\r\n•\tSFC’s representative shall be available to attend project kick off meeting with the Buyer to discuss project schedule, establish proper lines of communications, and other critical matters necessary to ensure a successful project.\r\n•\tSFC’s Project Manager shall be available for two day kick-off meeting at PEEIL HO (Gurgaon)/Bangalore. Travel expenses are included for this visit.\r\n•\tSFC shall provide all necessary support for approval of drawings/design from the end client/consultant and will visit to the client/consultant as on when required by PEEIPL representative at their expenses.\r\n•\tSFC shall provide supervision services of a field engineer(s) to assist with system start-up, commissioning and provide operator training for the SBR system. Skilled and un-skilled labor shall be provided by PEEIL as per the requirement of SFC.\t\r\n10.\tInspection\t\t•\tInspection shall be carried out at supplier’s manufacturing factory as per approved documents. Fooding, Lodging & Boarding, Accommodation.\r\n•\tTo and Fro Charges charges shall be borne by PEEIPL.\t\r\n11.\tSupport during operation and maintenance period.\t\t•\tSFC shall provide 2 visits yearly as and when required at site in order to adhere the performance guarantee. Any additional visits required by PEEIPL shall be on chargeable basis and will be paid extra at actuals.\t\r\n	SBR System Design\r\n\r\nThe SBR System shall be designed, including all related accessories, for biological treatment of wastewater with Raw water characteristics as shown in the table below. The Decanter shall decant clarified water as per the treated effluent quality characteristics table shown below. SFC shall assume suitable concentration for components in a biologically treated wastewater that is not given in the table below for designing the SBR system. SFC shall considered alum precipitates (for phosphorous precipitation) in the SBR tank while designing the system.\r\n	f	\N
